hy anyone might be upset by this.  It doesn't get near the value of CH, but it adds considerably to druid's and shamen's tank healing abilities.  I would love to see this spell in game.<br><br>*edit*  Something I thought of after I posted this...  I wonder, does the spell heal 75% of the person's hitpoints or does it heal them up to 75%?  Big difference.  If its 75% of their HP it is an awesome spell... if you healed them at 25% it would heal them to full.  If it heals them to 75% its still a great spell, but not quite as good.<br><br>*edit2* Spelling error... I've been hitting U instead of O all day... <p><center><br><br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=302961><img src=http://sanguinecrusaders.homestead.com/files/Akom_Sig.jpg></a> <br> <select name=Akom><option>Tradeskills<option>Master Smith 189 +5%<option>Master Tailor 183 +5%<option>Master Brewer 165<option>Master Fisherman 194<option>Master Potter 165<option>Master Baker 166<option>Master Fletcher 176<option> Master Jeweler 165</select></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uakomofcazicthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akom of Cazic Thule</A> at: 8/21/02 10:51:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugreystonethorngage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GreystoneThorngage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/21/02 9:22:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3082.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: More news from CR: Druids / Shamen ALMOST complete heal?</span><hr size=1> I had the same thoughts on that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utrimlock.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trimlock</A></span><b